---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const includes = [
  "Home page", "Service pages", "About page", "Contact page",
  "Mobile first design", "Google Maps integration", "Fast page speed",
  "Local SEO structure", "HTTPS security", "Analytics",
  "Quote request form", "Tap to call buttons", "Custom coding",
  "Google Business Profile integration",
];

const trades = [
  "General contractors", "Plumbers", "Electricians", "Roofers",
  "HVAC contractors", "Landscapers", "Concrete contractors", "Painters",
  "Remodelers", "Flooring contractors", "Commercial cleaning companies",
  "Building maintenance companies",
];

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Do you build websites for businesses in other states?",
    a: "Yes. I'm based in Big Bear, California, but I build websites for local service businesses all over the United States. Because everything is done by phone, email, and video call, we never need to meet in person and your location is never a problem. When we get on our first call, I learn your trade, the towns and counties you serve, and the kind of work you want more of. Then I build your website around those local searches, so the people in your area looking for your service have a better chance of finding you. Every website is built around your local market, your services, and the customers you're trying to reach, not around my location. So whether you're one town over or across the country, you get the same custom coded website, the same honest pricing, and the same person answering when you need something changed.",
  },
  {
    q: "What kinds of businesses do you work with?",
    a: "I build websites for local trade and service businesses of almost every kind: general contractors, plumbers, electricians, roofers, HVAC companies, landscapers, concrete crews, painters, remodelers, flooring pros, commercial cleaning companies, and building maintenance teams. The common thread is simple: if your customers find you by searching online and then calling, a website built the right way will bring you more of them. Your trade shapes how I build the site. A roofer needs storm damage and emergency repair pages; a landscaper needs seasonal services and a gallery of finished yards; a plumber needs a fast tap to call button because their customers are usually in a hurry. I build each site around the services you actually sell and the jobs you actually want, not a generic template with your logo dropped on top. If you're not sure whether your business fits, it almost certainly does. Book a free call, tell me what you do, and I'll tell you straight how a website would help you get found and get the call.",
  },
  {
    q: "How long does a website take?",
    a: "Most websites are live within about a week of our first call. That timeline assumes a standard site: a home page, your service pages, an about page, and a contact page, all built around your trade and service area. If your project is larger, with many service pages, multiple locations, online booking, or other automations, it takes a little longer, and I'll give you a real timeline in your proposal instead of a vague promise. The reason I can move quickly is that I build in clean code myself, so there's no committee, no account manager, and no back and forth with a team overseas. Once you approve the proposal, I get to work, send you a version to review, make your changes, and launch. You're involved at the points that matter and left alone the rest of the time so you can keep working. If you need it faster for a specific reason, like a busy season starting, tell me on the call and I'll be honest about what's possible.",
  },
  {
    q: "What if I already have a website?",
    a: "That's common, and you have two good options. The first is a full rebuild on the same domain. This is usually the better path if your current site is on Wix, Squarespace, GoDaddy, or another builder, because those sites are rented, hard to rank, and you never truly own them. I rebuild it in clean code that you own outright, keeping your domain and anything worth saving. The second option is a straight review. If you already have a decent site, I'll look at it and tell you honestly what's working, what's hurting you, and whether a rebuild is even worth your money. Sometimes the answer is that you only need a few fixes, and I'll say so rather than sell you something you don't need. Either way, the call is free and you walk away knowing where you stand. The one thing I'd caution against is leaving an outdated or slow website up while you decide, because for a busy service business, an old site can cost you jobs every week it stays online.",
  },
  {
    q: "What if I don't have photos or a logo?",
    a: "Not a problem at all, and it's never a reason to wait. Plenty of business owners come to me with no logo and no professional photos, and we launch anyway. If you don't have a logo, I can design a clean one for your business as part of the project. For photos, I use high quality stock images that fit your trade so the site looks professional from day one, and then we swap in real photos of your own work as you take them. Real photos of your finished jobs are powerful once you have them, because nothing sells your work like before and after shots of an actual project, so I'll show you the few simple shots worth grabbing on your phone. None of that has to be ready before we start. The goal is to get you online and getting calls quickly, not to stall the whole project because the photos aren't perfect yet. We launch with what we have, and the site only gets stronger as you add your own pictures and reviews over time.",
  },
  {
    q: "Do I own my website?",
    a: "When your website is finished, you own the code, your domain name, and your hosting account. Nothing is rented and you're never locked into a monthly website subscription. Most website builders work differently. You pay every month, but the website isn't truly yours. If you stop paying, the site often disappears. I build websites in clean code that you own outright. If you ever decide to work with someone else, you can. Your website belongs to your business, not to me.",
  },
  {
    q: "How much does a website cost?",
    a: "It depends on your business, so I won't throw out a number that turns out wrong. Here's the honest range you'll see in the market: on the cheap end, builders like Wix run around $30 a month forever, and you never own the site. On the high end, large agencies charge $10,000 or more, often with an ongoing monthly retainer attached. I build custom websites that you own outright and price them in between, with one clear number scoped to your business. What moves that number is straightforward: how many service pages you need, how many locations you serve, and whether you want extras like online booking, missed call text back, or lead tracking. Before I quote anything, I learn your trade and your service area on a free call, so the price reflects your actual business instead of a guess. You'll get a fixed proposal with exactly what's included and no surprises later. If you want the full breakdown of what goes into website pricing, I wrote a plain English guide on it, and then we can get on a call so I can give you your real number.",
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Websites for Contractors That Bring You More Calls"
  description="Custom websites for contractors and local trades, built for Google Search to turn calls into booked jobs. You own everything; no monthly rental. Built in the USA."
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Service",
      "name": "Website Design for Contractors",
      "serviceType": "Website design for contractors and local trades",
      "provider": { "@id": "https://reynahouse.ai/#org" },
      "areaServed": ["United States"],
      "description": "Custom coded websites for contractors and local trades, built for Google Search to convert callers into booked jobs. The owner keeps the code, domain, and hosting outright.",
      "url": "https://reynahouse.ai/websites-for-contractors/",
    })} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": faqs.map((f) => ({
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": f.q,
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a },
      })),
    })} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://reynahouse.ai/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Websites for Contractors", "item": "https://reynahouse.ai/websites-for-contractors/" },
      ],
    })} />
  </Fragment>

  <Header />

  <main class="page">
    <!-- HERO -->
    <article class="intro">
      <div class="intro__container">
        <nav class="crumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span aria-hidden="true">/</span> Websites for Contractors
        </nav>
        <span class="overline">BUILT FOR THE TRADES</span>
        <h1 class="h1">Websites for Contractors That Bring You More Calls</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          You do good work, but online the company with the better website
          usually gets the call. If customers can't find your business on Google,
          or they land on an outdated website, they often hire someone else before
          they ever speak with you.
        </p>
        <p class="body body--gold">
          Your website has one job: help customers find your business
          online and make it easy to call, request a quote, or schedule work.
          That's what every website I build is designed to do.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- WHAT YOU GET -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">What You Get</h2>
        <div class="cards">
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">Built for Google Search</h3>
            <p class="card__body">Every website is built around the searches your customers actually make; your trade, your services, your cities, and the work you want more of.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">Built to Get the Call</h3>
            <p class="card__body">Tap-to-call buttons, quote request forms, clear calls to action, and fast loading pages that make it easy for customers to contact you.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">Looks Like a Professional Business</h3>
            <p class="card__body">Clean, trustworthy design built specifically for trade businesses, not a recycled template.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">Mobile First Design</h3>
            <p class="card__body">Most customers find local businesses from their phone. Every website is designed for mobile first.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">You Own Everything</h3>
            <p class="card__body">You own the code, domain, hosting, and content. No subscriptions. No website rental.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3 class="card__title">Optional Growth Tools</h3>
            <p class="card__body">Add online booking, missed call text back, lead tracking, AI chat, and automations whenever you're ready.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- INCLUDES -->
    <section class="section section--tint">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">Every Website I Build Includes</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          {includes.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- BUILT FOR LOCAL SEARCH -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">Built for Local Search</h2>
        <p class="body">
          Most local service businesses don't need customers across the country;
          they need customers nearby.
        </p>
        <p class="body">
          Every website is structured around your service area so people searching
          for your trade in your city have a better chance of finding your business.
          Whether you serve one town or several counties, your website is built
          around the locations that matter most.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- COST -->
    <section class="section section--tint">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">What a Website Costs</h2>
        <p class="body">Every business is different.</p>
        <p class="body">
          Some websites cost $30 per month forever because you never own them.
          Others cost $10,000 or more through large agencies with ongoing retainers.
        </p>
        <p class="body">
          I build custom websites that you own outright. Before I give
          you a price, I learn about your trade, your service area, and what your
          business actually needs, so you receive one honest number with no
          surprises.
          <a class="inline-link" href="/small-business-website-cost/">See the full breakdown of what a website costs.</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHY DIFFERENT -->
    <section class="section section--dark">
      <div class="section__container">
        <span class="overline overline--light">WHY MINE IS DIFFERENT</span>
        <h2 class="h2 h2--light">Built in the USA, and You Own It</h2>
        <p class="body body--light">
          Many low cost website companies reduce prices by outsourcing development
          overseas or locking businesses into monthly website rentals.
        </p>
        <p class="body body--light">
          I build every website myself in the United States using clean code. When
          the project is finished, you own it. If you ever need help, I'm still
          here because I've earned your business, not because you're trapped.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHO I BUILD FOR -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">Who I Build Websites For</h2>
        <div class="trades">
          {trades.map((t) => <span class="trade">{t}</span>)}
        </div>
        <p class="body trades__note">
          If your business depends on local customers finding you online, I can
          build a website designed around that goal.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
    <section class="section section--tint">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">How It Works</h2>
        <div class="steps">
          <div class="step">
            <h3>Book a Free Call</h3>
            <p>Tell me about your trade, service area, and goals.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <h3>Receive a Fixed Proposal</h3>
            <p>You'll receive one clear price with exactly what's included.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <h3>Launch Your Website</h3>
            <p>Most websites are completed in about a week. After your review, your site launches under your ownership.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section section--cta">
      <div class="section__container">
        <h2 class="h2">Ready for More Calls?</h2>
        <p class="body">
          Tell me your trade and your service area, and I'll show you what a website
          built for Google Search can do for your business. Book a free call; no
          pressure, no obligation.
        </p>
        <div class="cta__actions">
          <a href="/#contact" class="btn btn--primary">Book a Free Call &rarr;</a>
          <a href="tel:+19093410243" class="btn btn--ghost">Or call 909-341-0243</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="section section--tint">
      <div class="section__container section__container--narrow">
        <h2 class="h2">Common Questions From Contractors</h2>
        {faqs.map((f) => (
          <details class="faq">
            <summary class="faq__q">{f.q}</summary>
            <p class="faq__a">{f.a}</p>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- RELATED -->
    <section class="related">
      <div class="related__container">
        <p class="related__title">Keep Reading</p>
        <div class="related__grid">
          <a class="related__card" href="/small-business-website-cost/">
            <span>What Does a Small Business Website Cost?</span>
            <small>The four ways to buy one, and the rent versus own trap.</small>
          </a>
          <a class="related__card" href="/missed-call-text-back/">
            <span>Missed Call Text Back</span>
            <small>Stop losing jobs to voicemail when you can't pick up.</small>
          </a>
          <a class="related__card" href="/why-not-showing-on-google/">
            <span>Why Isn't My Business on Google?</span>
            <small>The usual reasons, and how to fix them.</small>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .page { background-color: var(--white); }
  .intro { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--navy) 0%, #1a1a2e 100%); padding: 72px 24px 64px; }
  .intro__container { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .crumbs { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--tan); margin-bottom: 24px; }
  .crumbs a { color: var(--copper-light); }
  .crumbs a:hover { color: var(--copper); }
  .overline { display: block; font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: var(--copper-light); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .h1 { font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: var(--white); font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 6vw, 3.6rem); line-height: 1.05; margin-bottom: 24px; }
  .lede { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--white); font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section--tint { background-color: var(--cream); }
  .section--dark { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--forest) 0%, #1a2a1c 100%); }
  .section--cta { background-color: var(--white); text-align: center; }
  .section__container { max-width: 920px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section__container--narrow { max-width: 760px; }
  .h2 { font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: var(--navy); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4.5vw, 2.6rem); line-height: 1.1; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .h2--light { color: var(--white); }
  .body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--dark); font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .body--light { color: var(--cream); }
  .body--gold { color: var(--gold); font-weight: 600; }
  .inline-link { color: var(--copper-dark); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .inline-link:hover { color: var(--copper); }

  .cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px; margin-top: 28px; }
  .card { background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--tan); border-radius: 10px; padding: 24px; }
  .card__title { font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.5rem; letter-spacing: 0.02em; margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 1.1; }
  .card__body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--dark); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; }

  .checklist { list-style: none; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 10px 28px; margin-top: 24px; }
  .checklist li { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--dark); font-size: 1rem; padding: 6px 0 6px 28px; position: relative; }
  .checklist li::before { content: '✓'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--copper-dark); font-weight: 700; }

  .trades { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px; margin-top: 28px; }
  .trade { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--navy); background: var(--cream); border: 1px solid var(--tan); border-radius: 999px; padding: 8px 16px; }
  .trades__note { margin-top: 28px; }

  .steps { display: grid; gap: 16px; margin-top: 28px; counter-reset: step; }
  .step { position: relative; padding: 20px 20px 20px 68px; background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--tan); border-radius: 10px; }
  .step::before { counter-increment: step; content: counter(step); position: absolute; left: 20px; top: 20px; width: 34px; height: 34px; display: grid; place-items: center; background: var(--copper); color: var(--white); font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; font-size: 1.25rem; border-radius: 50%; }
  .step h3 { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .step p { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--dark); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; }

  .cta__actions { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 16px; justify-content: center; margin-top: 28px; }
  .btn { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1rem; padding: 14px 26px; border-radius: 8px; transition: background-color 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease; }
  .btn--primary { background-color: var(--copper); color: var(--white); }
  .btn--primary:hover { background-color: #b8843f; }
  .btn--ghost { border: 1px solid var(--navy); color: var(--navy); }
  .btn--ghost:hover { background-color: var(--navy); color: var(--white); }
  .btn:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--copper); outline-offset: 2px; }

  .faq { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--tan); padding: 16px 0; }
  .faq__q { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: var(--copper-dark); font-size: 0.95rem; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; padding: 4px 0; }
  .faq__q::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq__q::before { content: '+ '; font-weight: 700; }
  details[open] .faq__q::before { content: '− '; }
  .faq__a { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--navy); font-size: 0.97rem; line-height: 1.7; padding: 12px 0 4px; }

  .related { background: var(--cream); padding: 48px 24px; }
  .related__container { max-width: 920px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .related__title { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; color: var(--copper-dark); font-size: 0.85rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .related__grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 16px; }
  .related__card { display: block; background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--tan); border-radius: 10px; padding: 18px; transition: border-color 0.2s ease; }
  .related__card:hover { border-color: var(--copper); }
  .related__card span { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; color: var(--navy); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.3; }
  .related__card small { display: block; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: var(--dark); font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5; }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .checklist { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .related__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
